com.hp.autonomy.aci.content.identifier.stateid

Interface StateRange

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractStateRange, Range

    public interface StateRange
    A representation of the state range for a state id. The state range is the optional section in square brackets after the state token.

    This interface provides relatively few methods for manipulating a state range. This is intentional. Though the majority of ranges are continuous it is possible to have discontinuous ranges and these must also be supported.

      • isEmpty

        boolean isEmpty()
        Whether or not the range is empty. An empty range will have a size of 0 and an empty string representation.

        In general, implementations should be wary of allowing empty ranges to be created as they can cause confusion. Despite having a size of 0, an empty range will actually match all documents in a stored state, rather than none of them.

        Returns:
        true if the range is empty

      • size

        int size()
        The size of the range. For example, the range [5-7,12] has a size of 4. Note that a size of 0 signifies a range that will match all the documents in a stored state rather than one that will match no documents.
        Returns:
        The size of the range
